    public interface ICloseable
    Interface for objects which can have resources which must be explicitly closed (typically iterators).
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void close()
      Closes the object, releasing any associated resources.

    • Method Detail

      • close

        void close()
        Closes the object, releasing any associated resources. This method MAY be invoked safely if the object is already closed. Implementations of this interface MUST invoke close() once it is known that the object will no longer be used.
